(d)
In the event that any provision of this Contract shall be held invalid by any court
of competent jurisdiction, the remainder of this Contract shall be deemed to be severable and
shall continue in effect. The headings contained herein are for reference purposes only and shall
not in any way affect the meaning or interpretation of this Contract.
No provision of this Contract shall create or give any third party any claim or
right of action hereunder except as may specifically be provided herein in favor of Bank, its
successors and assigns.
(f)
All terms and words used in this Contract, regardless of number and gender, shall
be deemed and construed to include any other number, singular or plural, and any other gender,
masculine, feminine or neuter, as the context or sense of this Contract or any paragraph or clause
herein may require, the same as if such words have been fully and properly written.
(g)
All notices, writings and responses required or permitted to be given hereunder
shall be deemed to be effective when in writing and when delivered in person or when deposited
in the United States Mail as registered or certified mail, postage prepaid, with return receipt
requested, addressed to Contractor and Owner at the addresses set forth below.
(h)
Rights under this contract shall not be assigned by Contractor or Owner without
the prior written consent from the other party. This Contract shall be binding upon, and shall
inure to the benefit of, the parties hereto and their respective heirs, legal representatives,
successors and assigns, subject to' the foregoing limitation. Subcontracts for individual portions
of the work shall not be deemed an assignment of this Contract or any part thereof.
